sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M36132
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Self-assembles into a two-dimensional RNA scaffold with binding domains for MS2 and PP7 proteins. When presented with theophylline, the ribozyme should cleave the scaffold sequences, releasing the aptamers from the existing scaffold and preventing other scaffolds from forming.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vir Choksi, Daniel McHugh
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: RNA scaffold comes from Delebecque et al., Science 2011 Ribozyme switch comes from Win & Smolke, PNAS 2007
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The riboswitch was inserted into the scaffold sequence directly upstream of the aptamer. Spacers were used to prevent folding issues with the scaffold and ribozyme components of the transcripts.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M36128
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Encodes for the first part of a 2-dimensional self-assembling RNA scaffold.
d2' is a sequence followed by the PP7 binding domain. The 2D RNA assembly D2 forms from d2' and d2'', each followed by a distinct PP7 and MS2 aptamer. The dormant tile d2' spontaneously generates the pro-tile d2-1, which interacts with d2'' to generate tile d2-2. d2-2 then self-assembles into the 2D RNA scaffold D2 with PP7 and MS2 binding domains.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vir Choksi
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This part is only functional in the context of the other parts required for the 2D RNA scaffold.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M36129
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Encodes for an RNA sequence which functions as the binding domain for the PP7 bacteriophage coat protein.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Daniel McHugh
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: C. J. Delebecque, A. B. Lindner, P. A. Silver, F. A. Aldaye, ???Organization of intracellular reactions with rationally designed RNA assemblies??? Science 333, 470-474 (2011).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Can be used in the context of the one- and two-dimensional RNA scaffolds described in the Delebecque paper.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M36135
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Strong terminator from BIOFAB's terminator project
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vir Choksi
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Length similar to terminators used in Delebecque et al., Science 2011

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: spacer
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Generic spacer for ensuring a 70 bp distance between the end of the suffix of the BioBrick part containing the double terminator and the prefix of the BioBrick part containing the promoter of the new gene. Please, use the AlignX function of Vector NT to check for homology with the components in your plasmid before using this spacer.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S. Mahajan, Brian Chow, Peter Carr
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Randomly generated and optimized for several parameters (see Design notes).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
The size of the spacer was choosed to meet the minimum length of a sequence that can be queried using the BLAST search engine. However, subsequences of it can be used to design shorter spacers. The sequence was selected from many more sequences randomly generated using the Random DNA Generator engine; the GC% parameter used as input was 50%. The sequences were selected based on the following constraints listed in their order of importance: the absence of any putative promoter regions, a low degree of homology with the Elowitz plasmid (whose components are widely used in our designs), no homology with other E.coli sequences as shown by BLASTN search results and the presence of a number of TAA stop codons. The second constraint was the most stringent leading to the elimination of most sequences.

DE made the following changes to the original sequence in order to add stop codons in the -3 frame and more in the +2 frame (note, not all of these stop codons are UAA. Thus, if used in an organism that inserts an amino acid @ UGA or UAG the obvious will occur):
T->A @ 85
T->A @ 42
C->T @ 79
A->T @ 64
A->T @ 31
T->A @ 34
C->A @ 37
Also, note that the above changes further reduce (the already very weak) homology to current NCBI-stored sequences.

In the process of selecting the best sequence it appeared that a good alternative sequence for a spacer would be: AGGTTCTGATATGTAACTGTGCCCAATGTCGTTAGTGACGCATACCTCTTAAGAGGCCACTGTCCTAACA. The sequence contains no putative promoters and shows moderate homology with the 5' end of the Ampicillin resistance gene. However a strong promoter sequence starts 12 bp downstream of this sequence, and therefore the sequence presented above was preferred.

The sequence is compatible (does not show significant homology) with the components in the Elowitz repressilator plasmid.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M36136
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a rhamnose-inducible promoter. We used bases 1951-2101 from BBa_K564001. It is induced by 1000 micromolar rhamnose.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vir Choksi
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The rhamnose-inducible promoter is described in Giacolone et al., Biotechniques 2006. We used bases 1951-2101 from BBa_K564001.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M36130
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
d2'' is the second part required for formation of the 2-dimensional RNA scaffold.
The 2D RNA assembly D2 forms from d2' and d2'', each followed by a distinct PP7 and MS2 aptamer. The dormant tile d2' spontaneously generates the pro-tile d2-1, which interacts with d2'' to generate tile d2-2. d2-2 then self-assembles into the 2D RNA scaffold D2 with PP7 and MS2 binding domains.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vir Choksi
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: d2'' is only functional when used along with other parts required for the 2D RNA scaffold.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Daniel McHugh
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: C. J. Delebecque, A. B. Lindner, P. A. Silver, F. A. Aldaye, ???Organization of intracellular reactions with rationally designed RNA assemblies??? Science 333, 470-474 (2011).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Can be used in the context of the one- and two- dimensional RNA scaffolds described in the Delebecque paper.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M36126
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Ribozyme that self-cleaves in the presence of theophylline.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Daniel McHugh
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: M. N. Win, C. D. Smolke, ???A modular and extensible RNA-based gene-regulatory platform for engineering cellular function??? PNAS 36, 14283-14288 (2007).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The part includes two brief spacer sequences to ensure functionality over a range of transcript contexts.
